1- Install docker
2- Create a Docker-compose file and Use file available in the repo
    i- Change env for setting up MYSQL
        MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: <PASSWORD>
        MYSQL_DATABASE: <DB_NAME>
        MYSQL_USER: <DB_USER_NAME>
        MYSQL_PASSWORD: <DB_PASSWORD>
    
    ii- Change env to for setting up WORDPRESS same as MYSQL env

3- Execute "docker compose up -d"
4- After installing head to the url ip:port and install wordpress and
    set the url by logging into wp-admin ->settings->general 
    and change the domain URL. so that wordpress can be accessed using the url.

5- Now headover to nginx and use this nginx config located in the repo